Package: rmdTemplates
Type: Package
Title: A collection of Rmarkdown templates
Version: 0.6.2
Author: F. Rodriguez-Sanchez <f.rodriguez.sanc@gmail.com>. Some templates 
    modified from original templates by Carl Boettiger and Jeff Hollister.
Maintainer: F. Rodriguez-Sanchez <f.rodriguez.sanc@gmail.com>
Description: A collection of Rmarkdown templates. Includes templates for 
    writing scientific manuscripts, manuscript reviews, and other Rmarkdown documents, 
    with support for citations and different bibliography styles. It also includes 
    functions to embed data and Rmarkdown source files within HTML files. 
    After installing the package, click on `create new Rmarkdown document` in
    Rstudio to have access to the templates. See https://rmarkdown.rstudio.com/
    for more information.
License: CC0
URL: https://github.com/Pakillo/rmdTemplates
BugReports: https://github.com/Pakillo/rmdTemplates/issues
Imports:
    base64enc,
    knitr,
    knitcitations,
    rmarkdown
Suggests:
    devtools
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
